## CONTEXT

DynamoUI scaffolds skill YAML files from a live PostgreSQL schema.
The current scaffolder produces structurally correct but semantically
empty output — field descriptions are blank, business_description is
a TODO placeholder, and generated patterns are generic (list all,
search by field).

This brief adds two things:
  1. Extract PostgreSQL table/column comments during scaffolding and
     map them into skill YAML fields, including a [semantic:X] tag
     convention parsed from column comments.
  2. Accept a CLI input file of role-based query examples that, combined
     with the enriched schema context, drives the LLM pattern seeder to
     produce business-meaningful patterns and widgets instead of generic ones.

These two features together eliminate the need for post-scaffold manual
enrichment of business_description and field descriptions, and produce
a pattern cache that reflects real business use cases from day one.

---

## FEATURE 1 — PostgreSQL comment extraction

### What to build

The SchemaInspector currently returns column descriptors with four fields:
name, type, nullable, is_pk. Extend it to also return:
  - table_comment: the table-level COMMENT ON TABLE value (string or empty)
  - column comment: per-column COMMENT ON COLUMN value (string or empty)

SQLAlchemy's inspect() already retrieves these via get_table_comment() for
the table and the "comment" key in get_columns() results for columns.
No new dependencies are needed.

### Semantic tag convention

Column comments may contain a bracketed semantic tag anywhere in the text:
  [semantic:time_series]
  [semantic:metric]
  [semantic:status]
  [semantic:identifier]
  [semantic:label]

The extractor must parse this tag out of the comment text, store it
separately as a "semantic" field on the column descriptor, and strip the
tag from the human-readable comment text before it becomes the field
description. If no tag is present, semantic is null.

Valid semantic values: time_series, metric, status, identifier, label.
Any unrecognised tag value is ignored (treated as null) with a warning logged.

### Mapping into skill YAML

  table_comment        → entity.business_description
  column comment text  → field.description  (after tag stripped)
  column semantic tag  → field.semantic

If table_comment is empty, business_description is omitted from the
generated YAML (do not write a TODO placeholder — omit the key entirely).
If a column comment is empty, field.description is omitted.

business_description and field.semantic are new optional fields on the
EntitySkill and FieldDef Pydantic models. Both default to empty/null so
all existing skill files remain valid with no changes.

### LLM context enrichment

The schema context string passed to the LLM (used in QuerySynthesiser and
PatternSeeder) must be updated to include these new fields when present:

  Current format:
    Entity: Invoice (table: Invoice)
    Fields: InvoiceId (integer PK), CustomerId (integer), Total (float)

  Enriched format (when comments exist):
    Entity: Invoice (table: Invoice)
    Business context: Sales invoice raised when a customer completes a
    purchase. Primary revenue record used for monthly reporting.
    Fields:
      InvoiceId (integer PK, identifier)
      CustomerId (integer, identifier)
      InvoiceDate (date, time_series) — Date purchase completed, used for trend analysis
      Total (float, metric) — Total invoice value in USD, primary revenue metric

Sensitive fields are always excluded regardless of comment content.
This rule is pre-existing and must not be relaxed.

